# UI & Component Rules

## Layout
The main editor page follows a 3-panel layout inspired by Postmark:

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  Header: Template Name | Subject | Save button          │
├──────────────┬──────────────────────────────────────────┤
│  Sidebar     │  [Edit] [Preview] tabs                   │
│  (template   ├──────────────────┬───────────────────────┤
│   list)      │  Code Editor     │  Preview / Mock Data  │
│              │  (HTML | Text)   │  Panel                │
└──────────────┴──────────────────┴───────────────────────┘
```

- Sidebar: fixed 260px width, scrollable template list
- Editor panel: resizable, left half
- Preview panel: right half, toggleable between Preview and MockData

## Code Editor (CodeMirror)
- Use `@uiw/react-codemirror` with `@codemirror/lang-html`
- Theme: dark (use `vscodeDark` or `dracula`)
- Enable: line numbers, auto-close brackets, fold gutter
- Tab size: 2 spaces
- On every change, debounce 200ms before updating the store

## Tabs
The editor has two tabs: `HTML` and `Text` (plain text version of the email).
The preview panel has two tabs: `Preview` and `Mock Data`.

## Template List (Sidebar)
- Show template `name` and `alias` 
- Active template highlighted
- "New Template" button at the top
- Each item has a delete button (show confirmation popover before deleting)
- Search/filter input to filter by name or alias

## Mock Data Panel
- Full-height JSON editor using CodeMirror with `@codemirror/lang-json`
- Show a "Variables detected" badge listing all `{{variables}}` found in the current HTML
- "Auto-fill missing keys" button that adds `null` values for any detected variable not yet in mock data
- Validate JSON on every change — show inline error at the top of the panel

## Notifications / Toast
- Use a lightweight toast library (`sonner`) for success/error feedback
- Success: "Template saved", "Template deleted"
- Error: "Failed to save template", "Invalid JSON in mock data"

## Tailwind
- Use Tailwind utility classes only — no inline `style` except for dynamic values (e.g., iframe width)
- Prefer `clsx` or `cn` helper for conditional class merging
- Color palette: dark editor theme — bg-gray-950 / bg-gray-900 / bg-gray-800 surfaces
- Accent color: orange-500 (matching Postmark's CTA style)

## Accessibility
- All interactive elements must have accessible labels (`aria-label` or visible text)
- Keyboard navigation must work: Ctrl+S to save, Ctrl+/ to toggle preview/editor
